{
  "dssSchemaVersion": 4,

  "language": {
    "name":           "CSubset",
    "version":        "0.1.0",
    "fileExtensions": [".c", ".h"]
  },

  "artifactProfiles": ["cli", "lib", "staticlib"],

  "imports": {
    "strategy":        "include-following",
    "directiveRule":   "includeDirective",
    "pathToken":       "StringStart",
    "systemPathToken": "HeaderStart"
  },

  "lexerModes": {
    "main":          { "tokens": "default" },
    "string":        { "defaultToken": { "kind": "StringLiteral", "coalesce": true } },
    "charBody":      { "defaultToken": { "kind": "CharLiteral",   "coalesce": true } },

    "include-directive": {
      "tokens": {
        "<": [{
          "kind": "HeaderStart",
          "modeOp": "replaceMode", "modeArg": "header-body",
          "stringStyle": { "escapeKind": "none", "endsAt": ">" }
        }]
      },
      "popAtNewline": true
    },
    "header-body":   { "defaultToken": { "kind": "HeaderPath",    "coalesce": true } },
    "line-comment":  {
      "defaultToken":    { "kind": "CommentChar", "flags": ["EmptySpace"] },
      "unterminatedAs":  "comment"
    },
    "block-comment": {
      "defaultToken":    { "kind": "CommentChar", "flags": ["EmptySpace"] },
      "unterminatedAs":  "comment"
    }
  },

  "$fc2CastExprComment": "FC2 Part A: C-style cast `(type)expr` (castExpr/castTypeRef/castTypeBase/castOperand shapes). castExpr shares the `( ... )` opener with compoundLiteralExpr/parenExpr inside the speculative operand alt; the probe disambiguates structurally (a brace-init follows the compound literal's `)`, an expression follows the cast's). `commitRequiresTypeName` names the type-position child rule: a structurally-successful probe COMMITS only per the parser's GENERIC type-name triage — (1) a type that is NOT a lone Identifier (keyword/struct-tag/star/const present) always commits, those forms cannot be expressions; (2) a lone Identifier the binder sketch knows as a TYPE commits; (3) one it knows as a VALUE rolls back to the value reading (shadowing-aware); (4) an UNKNOWN lone Identifier commits iff the token after the type's closer is NOT an infix/postfix/ternary operator per the operator table (the value reading could not continue), else rolls back AND records an AmbiguousTypeNameCandidate for the compilation-unit oracle's one-shot reparse (cross-file typedefs). castTypeRef duplicates typeRefAllowingStruct PLUS a bare-Identifier base (typedef names in cast position) — deliberately NOT added to typeRefAllowingStruct itself, which would inject the C decl-vs-expr statement ambiguity (`T x;` vs `a * b;`) into varDecl/param/structField; that generalization stays anchored separately. castOperand is a second expr-entry rule re-entering the Pratt walker at PREFIX precedence (90): the cast operand binds prefix + postfix operators but NOT binary/ternary ones, giving C-correct `(int)a + b` == ((int)a)+b, `(int)x[2]` == (int)(x[2]), `-(int)x`, and `(int)(long)x` chains. Same wrapper vocabulary as `expression` (wrapper rule names are per-schema; the loader dedups).",

  "$ff11AngleIncludeComment": "FF11 angle-include lexing. `#` pushes the line-scoped `include-directive` mode (popAtNewline:true -> the frame auto-pops at the next newline, so a malformed `#include` with no header -- or any directive -- never leaks `<`-as-header-opener into the following line; C preprocessor directives are line-oriented). That mode inherits the top-level token map (tokens:default) so `include`, `\"...\"`, and identifiers all lex normally; the ONLY override is `<`, which there OPENS a header path (replaceMode -> header-body, stringStyle.endsAt `>`) instead of meaning LtOp. The override-first longest-match rule (language-config-spec section 9.6) means `<` wins at length 1 and the global `<<`/`<=` are deliberately suppressed inside a directive -- correct, since `#include <<x>>` is not valid C. The `header-body` mode mirrors the `string` body: a coalesced `HeaderPath` token captures the raw path bytes between `<` and the closing `>` (which pops the frame back to main); escapeKind:none -- header paths have no escapes. The quote form keeps the global `\"`->StringStart->string body unchanged (additive: both `#include <h>` and `#include \"h\"` work). The resolver reads the raw path slice (a filename, not a decoded string) for both forms, and picks the search path by which token kind it finds under the directive (imports.pathToken=StringStart -> self-dir+includeDirs; imports.systemPathToken=HeaderStart -> shippedLibDirs).",

  "tokens": {
    " ":  [{ "kind": "Whitespace", "flags": ["EmptySpace"] }],
    "\t": [{ "kind": "Whitespace", "flags": ["EmptySpace"] }],
    "\n": [{ "kind": "Newline",    "flags": ["EmptySpace"] }],
    "\r": [{ "kind": "Whitespace", "flags": ["EmptySpace"] }],

    "//": [{
      "kind": "LineCommentStart", "flags": ["EmptySpace"],
      "modeOp": "pushMode", "modeArg": "line-comment",
      "stringStyle": { "escapeKind": "none", "endsAt": "\n" }
    }],
    "/*": [{
      "kind": "BlockCommentStart", "flags": ["EmptySpace"],
      "modeOp": "pushMode", "modeArg": "block-comment",
      "stringStyle": { "escapeKind": "none", "endsAt": "*/" }
    }],

    "(":  [{ "kind": "ParenOpen",     "opensScope": "Paren"   }],
    ")":  [{ "kind": "ParenClose",    "closesScope": true     }],
    "{":  [{ "kind": "BlockOpen",     "opensScope": "Block"   }],
    "}":  [{ "kind": "BlockClose",    "closesScope": true     }],
    "[":  [{ "kind": "BracketOpen",   "opensScope": "Bracket" }],
    "]":  [{ "kind": "BracketClose",  "closesScope": true     }],

    ";":  [{ "kind": "EndStatement" }],
    ",":  [{ "kind": "Comma" }],
    ":":  [{ "kind": "Colon" }],

    "#": [{ "kind": "HashOp", "modeOp": "pushMode", "modeArg": "include-directive" }],
    "\"": [{
      "kind": "StringStart",
      "modeOp": "pushMode", "modeArg": "string",
      "stringStyle": { "escapeKind": "char", "escapeChar": "\\", "endsAt": "\"" }
    }],
    "'": [{
      "kind": "CharStart",
      "modeOp": "pushMode", "modeArg": "charBody",
      "stringStyle": { "escapeKind": "char", "escapeChar": "\\", "endsAt": "'" }
    }],

    "=":  [{ "kind": "AssignOp" }],
    "+":  [{ "kind": "PlusOp"   }],
    "-":  [{ "kind": "MinusOp"  }],
    "*":  [{ "kind": "StarOp"   }],
    "/":  [{ "kind": "SlashOp"  }],
    "%":  [{ "kind": "PercentOp" }],
    "!":  [{ "kind": "BangOp"   }],
    "?":  [{ "kind": "QuestionOp" }],

    "==": [{ "kind": "EqEqOp" }],
    "!=": [{ "kind": "NotEqOp" }],
    "<":  [{ "kind": "LtOp" }],
    ">":  [{ "kind": "GtOp" }],
    "<=": [{ "kind": "LtEqOp" }],
    ">=": [{ "kind": "GtEqOp" }],
    "&&": [{ "kind": "AndAndOp" }],
    "||": [{ "kind": "OrOrOp"  }],

    "&":  [{ "kind": "BitAndOp" }],
    "|":  [{ "kind": "BitOrOp"  }],
    "^":  [{ "kind": "BitXorOp" }],
    "~":  [{ "kind": "TildeOp"  }],
    "<<": [{ "kind": "ShlOp"    }],
    ">>": [{ "kind": "ShrOp"    }],

    "++": [{ "kind": "PlusPlusOp" }],
    "--": [{ "kind": "MinusMinusOp" }],

    ".":  [{ "kind": "DotOp"   }],
    "->": [{ "kind": "ArrowOp" }],
    "...":[{ "kind": "EllipsisOp" }],

    "+=":  [{ "kind": "PlusAssignOp"   }],
    "-=":  [{ "kind": "MinusAssignOp"  }],
    "*=":  [{ "kind": "StarAssignOp"   }],
    "/=":  [{ "kind": "SlashAssignOp"  }],
    "%=":  [{ "kind": "ModAssignOp"    }],
    "&=":  [{ "kind": "BitAndAssignOp" }],
    "|=":  [{ "kind": "BitOrAssignOp"  }],
    "^=":  [{ "kind": "BitXorAssignOp" }],
    "<<=": [{ "kind": "ShlAssignOp"    }],
    ">>=": [{ "kind": "ShrAssignOp"    }]
  },

  "operators": {
    "groups": [
      { "precedence": 15, "associativity": "right",                      "operators": ["=", "+=", "-=", "*=", "/=", "%=", "&=", "|=", "^=", "<<=", ">>="] },
      { "precedence": 16, "associativity": "right", "arity": "ternary",   "operators": ["?"], "middle": ":"                       },
      { "precedence": 20, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["||"]                                   },
      { "precedence": 25, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["&&"]                                   },
      { "precedence": 30, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["|"]                                    },
      { "precedence": 35, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["^"]                                    },
      { "precedence": 40, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["&"]                                    },
      { "precedence": 50, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["==", "!="]                             },
      { "precedence": 55, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["<", ">", "<=", ">="]                   },
      { "precedence": 60, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["<<", ">>"]                             },
      { "precedence": 65, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["+", "-"]                               },
      { "precedence": 70, "associativity": "left",                       "operators": ["*", "/", "%"]                          },
      { "precedence": 90, "associativity": "right", "arity": "prefix",   "operators": ["!", "~", "-", "*", "&"]                },
      { "precedence": 95,                            "arity": "postfix",  "operators": ["++", "--"]                            },
      { "precedence": 100,                           "arity": "postfix",  "operators": ["("], "endsAt": ")", "bodyRule": "argList" },
      { "precedence": 100,                           "arity": "postfix",  "operators": ["["], "endsAt": "]", "bodyRule": "expression" },
      { "precedence": 100,                           "arity": "postfix",  "operators": ["."],  "followerRule": "memberFollower" },
      { "precedence": 100,                           "arity": "postfix",  "operators": ["->"], "followerRule": "memberFollower" }
    ]
  },

  "numberStyle": {
    "decimal": true,
    "integerPrefixes": [
      { "prefix": "0x", "radix": 16, "digits": "0-9a-fA-F",
        "float": { "exponent": { "letters": ["p", "P"], "signOptional": true },
                   "exponentDigits": "0-9" } },
      { "prefix": "0X", "radix": 16, "digits": "0-9a-fA-F",
        "float": { "exponent": { "letters": ["p", "P"], "signOptional": true },
                   "exponentDigits": "0-9" } },
      { "prefix": "0b", "radix": 2,  "digits": "01"        },
      { "prefix": "0B", "radix": 2,  "digits": "01"        },
      { "prefix": "0o", "radix": 8,  "digits": "0-7"       },
      { "prefix": "0O", "radix": 8,  "digits": "0-7"       },
      { "prefix": "0",  "radix": 8,  "digits": "0-7"       }
    ],
    "exponent":         { "letters": ["e", "E"], "signOptional": true },
    "fractionPoint":    ".",
    "trailingFraction": true,
    "leadingFraction":  true,
    "digitSeparator":   "'",
    "integerSuffixes":  ["u", "U", "l", "L", "ll", "LL", "ul", "UL", "lu", "LU",
                          "ull", "ULL", "llu", "LLU"],
    "floatSuffixes":    ["f", "F"],
    "emitKind":         { "integer": "IntLiteral", "float": "FloatLiteral" }
  },

  "syncTokens": ["EndStatement", "BlockClose"],

  "keywords": [
    { "word": "include", "kind": "IncludeKeyword" },

    { "word": "void",    "kind": "VoidKeyword"    },
    { "word": "int",     "kind": "IntKeyword"     },
    { "word": "long",    "kind": "LongKeyword"    },
    { "word": "char",    "kind": "CharKeyword"    },
    { "word": "short",    "kind": "ShortKeyword"      },
    { "word": "unsigned", "kind": "UnsignedKeyword"   },
    { "word": "signed",   "kind": "SignedKeyword"     },
    { "word": "bool",     "kind": "BoolKeyword"       },
    { "word": "_Bool",    "kind": "LegacyBoolKeyword" },
    { "word": "true",     "kind": "TrueKeyword"       },
    { "word": "false",    "kind": "FalseKeyword"      },
    { "word": "float",    "kind": "FloatKeyword"      },
    { "word": "double",   "kind": "DoubleKeyword"     },
    { "word": "const",   "kind": "ConstKeyword"   },
    { "word": "typedef", "kind": "TypedefKeyword" },
    { "word": "struct",  "kind": "StructKeyword"  },
    { "word": "union",   "kind": "UnionKeyword"   },
    { "word": "enum",    "kind": "EnumKeyword"    },

    { "word": "if",      "kind": "IfKeyword"      },
    { "word": "else",    "kind": "ElseKeyword"    },
    { "word": "while",   "kind": "WhileKeyword"   },
    { "word": "do",      "kind": "DoKeyword"      },
    { "word": "for",     "kind": "ForKeyword"     },
    { "word": "return",  "kind": "ReturnKeyword"  },
    { "word": "switch",  "kind": "SwitchKeyword"  },
    { "word": "case",    "kind": "CaseKeyword"    },
    { "word": "default", "kind": "DefaultKeyword" },
    { "word": "break",    "kind": "BreakKeyword"    },
    { "word": "continue", "kind": "ContinueKeyword" },

    { "word": "extern",  "kind": "ExternKeyword"  },

    { "word": "static",        "kind": "StaticKeyword"    },
    { "word": "__attribute__", "kind": "AttributeKeyword" }
  ],

  "shapes": {
    "root": { "sequence": [ { "repeat": "topLevel" } ] },

    "topLevel": {
      "alt": [
        "includeDirective",
        "typedefDecl",
        "structDecl",
        "unionDecl",
        "enumDecl",
        "topLevelDecl",
        "externDecl"
      ]
    },

    "structDecl": {
      "sequence": [
        "StructKeyword", "Identifier",
        "BlockOpen",
        { "repeat": "structField" },
        "BlockClose",
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "structField": {
      "sequence": [ "typeRefAllowingStruct", "Identifier", "EndStatement" ]
    },

    "structTypeRef": {
      "sequence": [ "StructKeyword", "Identifier" ]
    },

    "unionDecl": {
      "sequence": [
        "UnionKeyword", "Identifier",
        "BlockOpen",
        { "repeat": "unionField" },
        "BlockClose",
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "unionField": {
      "sequence": [ "typeRefAllowingStruct", "Identifier", "EndStatement" ]
    },

    "unionTypeRef": {
      "sequence": [ "UnionKeyword", "Identifier" ]
    },

    "enumDecl": {
      "sequence": [
        "EnumKeyword", "Identifier",
        "BlockOpen",
        { "optional": {
            "sequence": [
              "enumerator",
              { "repeat": { "sequence": [ "Comma", { "optional": "enumerator" } ] } }
            ]
        }},
        "BlockClose",
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "enumerator": {
      "sequence": [
        "Identifier",
        { "optional": { "sequence": [ "AssignOp", "expression" ] } }
      ]
    },

    "enumTypeRef": {
      "sequence": [ "EnumKeyword", "Identifier" ]
    },

    "memberFollower": {
      "sequence": [ "Identifier" ]
    },

    "topLevelDecl": {
      "sequence": [ { "optional": "declSpecifiers" }, "typeRef", "Identifier", "topLevelDeclTail" ]
    },

    "declSpecifiers": {
      "sequence": [ "singleDeclSpecifier", { "repeat": "singleDeclSpecifier" } ]
    },
    "singleDeclSpecifier": {
      "alt": [ "StaticKeyword", "attrSpec" ]
    },
    "attrSpec": {
      "sequence": [ "AttributeKeyword", "ParenOpen", "ParenOpen", { "optional": "Identifier" }, "ParenClose", "ParenClose" ]
    },

    "topLevelDeclTail": {
      "alt": [ "funcDefTail", "varDeclTail" ]
    },

    "funcDefTail": {
      "sequence": [ "funcParams", "block" ]
    },

    "funcParams": {
      "sequence": [ "ParenOpen", { "optional": "paramList" }, "ParenClose" ]
    },

    "typedefDecl": {
      "sequence": [ "TypedefKeyword", "typeRefAllowingStruct", "Identifier", "EndStatement" ]
    },

    "includeDirective": {
      "sequence": [ "HashOp", "IncludeKeyword", "includeTarget" ]
    },

    "includeTarget": {
      "alt": [ "includeQuoteTarget", "includeAngleTarget" ]
    },
    "includeQuoteTarget": {
      "sequence": [ "StringStart", "StringLiteral" ]
    },
    "includeAngleTarget": {
      "sequence": [ "HeaderStart", "HeaderPath" ]
    },

    "externDecl": {
      "sequence": [
        "ExternKeyword",
        "typeRef",
        "Identifier",
        "externTail"
      ]
    },

    "externFuncTail": {
      "sequence": [
        "ParenOpen",
        { "optional": "paramList" },
        "ParenClose",
        { "optional": "stringLiteralExpr" },
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "externTail": {
      "alt": [
        "externFuncTail",
        "varDeclTail"
      ]
    },

    "varDeclTail": {
      "sequence": [
        { "optional": "arrayDeclSuffix" },
        { "optional": { "sequence": [ "AssignOp", "initValue" ] } },
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "initValue": { "alt": [ "braceInitList", "expression" ] },

    "arrayDeclSuffix": {
      "sequence": [
        "BracketOpen",
        { "optional": "expression" },
        "BracketClose"
      ]
    },

    "typeSpecifierSeq": {
      "$comment": "FC3 c1: C 6.7.2 type-specifier run — one-or-more specifier KEYWORDS in any order (`unsigned long long int` == `long long unsigned int` == `long unsigned long`). The inner alt is INLINE (no named wrapper rule) so the matched keyword TOKENS land as typeSpecifierSeq's DIRECT children — the semantic engine's multiset arm requires all-token children. Which multisets are VALID (and what core each resolves to, per data model) is the semantics.typeSpecifiers table; invalid combos (`unsigned float`, `short long`) parse fine here and reject SEMANTICALLY by absence from the table (S_InvalidTypeSpecifierCombination). The seq SUBSUMES the former single-token Void/Int/Long/Char alts (a one-keyword run). Keyword-led, so castExpr's commitRequiresTypeName triage rule 1 (not-a-lone-identifier) always commits a seq-led cast type.",
      "sequence": [
        { "alt": [ "VoidKeyword", "IntKeyword", "LongKeyword", "CharKeyword", "ShortKeyword", "UnsignedKeyword", "SignedKeyword", "BoolKeyword", "LegacyBoolKeyword", "FloatKeyword", "DoubleKeyword" ] },
        { "repeat": { "alt": [ "VoidKeyword", "IntKeyword", "LongKeyword", "CharKeyword", "ShortKeyword", "UnsignedKeyword", "SignedKeyword", "BoolKeyword", "LegacyBoolKeyword", "FloatKeyword", "DoubleKeyword" ] } }
      ]
    },

    "typeBase": { "alt": [ "typeSpecifierSeq", "Identifier" ] },

    "typeRef": {
      "sequence": [
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" },
        "typeBase",
        { "repeat": "StarOp" },
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" }
      ]
    },

    "typeBaseAllowingStruct": {
      "alt": [ "typeSpecifierSeq", "structTypeRef", "unionTypeRef", "enumTypeRef" ]
    },

    "typeRefAllowingStruct": {
      "sequence": [
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" },
        "typeBaseAllowingStruct",
        { "repeat": "StarOp" },
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" }
      ]
    },

    "varDeclHead": {
      "sequence": [
        "typeRefAllowingStruct",
        "Identifier",
        { "optional": "arrayDeclSuffix" },
        { "optional": { "sequence": [ "AssignOp", "initValue" ] } }
      ]
    },

    "varDecl": { "sequence": [ "varDeclHead", "EndStatement" ] },

    "paramList": {
      "sequence": [
        "param",
        { "repeat": { "sequence": [ "Comma", "paramOrEllipsis" ] } }
      ]
    },

    "param": { "sequence": [ "typeRefAllowingStruct", "Identifier" ] },

    "paramOrEllipsis": {
      "alt": [
        "param",
        "ellipsisParam"
      ]
    },
    "ellipsisParam": { "sequence": [ "EllipsisOp" ] },

    "block": {
      "sequence": [
        "BlockOpen",
        { "repeat": "statement" },
        "BlockClose"
      ]
    },

    "statement": {
      "alt": [
        "varDecl",
        "block",
        "ifStmt",
        "whileStmt",
        "doStmt",
        "forStmt",
        "switchStmt",
        "breakStmt",
        "continueStmt",
        "returnStmt",
        "exprStmt"
      ]
    },

    "ifStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "IfKeyword",
        "ParenOpen", "expression", "ParenClose",
        "statement",
        { "optional": { "sequence": [ "ElseKeyword", "statement" ] } }
      ]
    },

    "whileStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "WhileKeyword",
        "ParenOpen", "expression", "ParenClose",
        "statement"
      ]
    },

    "doStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "DoKeyword",
        "statement",
        "WhileKeyword",
        "ParenOpen", "expression", "ParenClose",
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "forStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "ForKeyword",
        "ParenOpen",
        { "optional": { "alt": [ "varDeclHead", "expression" ] } },
        "EndStatement",
        { "optional": "expression" },
        "EndStatement",
        { "optional": "expression" },
        "ParenClose",
        "statement"
      ]
    },

    "returnStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "ReturnKeyword",
        { "optional": "expression" },
        "EndStatement"
      ]
    },

    "breakStmt":    { "sequence": [ "BreakKeyword",    "EndStatement" ] },
    "continueStmt": { "sequence": [ "ContinueKeyword", "EndStatement" ] },

    "switchStmt": {
      "sequence": [
        "SwitchKeyword",
        "ParenOpen", "expression", "ParenClose",
        "BlockOpen",
        { "repeat": "switchBodyItem" },
        "BlockClose"
      ]
    },

    "switchBodyItem": { "alt": [ "caseLabel", "statement" ] },

    "caseLabel": {
      "alt": [
        { "sequence": [ "CaseKeyword", "expression", "Colon" ] },
        { "sequence": [ "DefaultKeyword", "Colon" ] }
      ]
    },


    "exprStmt": { "sequence": [ "expression", "EndStatement" ] },

    "expression": {
      "expr": {
        "atom": "operand",
        "wrapperRules": {
          "binary":  "binaryExpr",
          "unary":   "unaryExpr",
          "postfix": "postfixExpr",
          "ternary": "ternaryExpr"
        }
      }
    },

    "operand": {
      "alt": [
        "Identifier",
        "IntLiteral",
        "FloatLiteral",
        "TrueKeyword",
        "FalseKeyword",
        "stringLiteralExpr",
        "charLiteralExpr",
        "compoundLiteralExpr",
        "castExpr",
        "parenExpr"
      ],
      "speculative": true,
      "$lookaheadComment": "FC2 Part A: raised 8 -> 64. The speculation budget is lookahead*16 tokens per probe (parser SpeculationProbe); a castExpr probe must consume the ENTIRE cast operand expression before its frame closes, so the old 128-token budget was a correctness cliff for casts of long expressions (and for large compound-literal brace inits). 64 -> 1024-token probe budget.",
      "lookahead": 64
    },

    "parenExpr": { "sequence": [ "ParenOpen", "expression", "ParenClose" ] },

    "compoundLiteralExpr": {
      "sequence": [ "ParenOpen", "typeRefAllowingStruct", "ParenClose", "braceInitList" ]
    },

    "castExpr": {
      "sequence": [ "ParenOpen", "castTypeRef", "ParenClose", "castOperand" ],
      "commitRequiresTypeName": "castTypeRef"
    },

    "castTypeBase": {
      "alt": [ "typeSpecifierSeq", "Identifier", "structTypeRef", "unionTypeRef", "enumTypeRef" ]
    },

    "castTypeRef": {
      "sequence": [
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" },
        "castTypeBase",
        { "repeat": "StarOp" },
        { "optional": "ConstKeyword" }
      ]
    },

    "castOperand": {
      "expr": {
        "atom": "operand",
        "minPrecedence": 90,
        "wrapperRules": {
          "binary":  "binaryExpr",
          "unary":   "unaryExpr",
          "postfix": "postfixExpr",
          "ternary": "ternaryExpr"
        }
      }
    },

    "braceInitList": {
      "sequence": [
        "BlockOpen",
        { "optional": {
            "sequence": [
              "initElement",
              { "repeat": { "sequence": [ "Comma", { "optional": "initElement" } ] } }
            ]
        }},
        "BlockClose"
      ]
    },

    "initElement": {
      "alt": [
        { "sequence": [
            "designator",
            { "repeat": "designator" },
            "AssignOp",
            "initValue"
        ]},
        "initValue"
      ]
    },

    "designator": { "alt": [ "designatedField", "designatedIndex" ] },
    "designatedField": { "sequence": [ "DotOp", "Identifier" ] },
    "designatedIndex": { "sequence": [ "BracketOpen", "expression", "BracketClose" ] },

